com.kinvey.persistence
Interface Entity<T>

Type Parameters:
T - Typically a EntityDict
All Known Implementing Classes:
EntityDict, KinveyUserImpl
public interface Entity<T>

Used to retrieve single object instances (usually EntityDict) from Kinvey's appdata API.

Method Detail

deleteAll

void deleteAll()
               throws KinveyException
Deletes the entire collection. This should be used with caution.

Throws:
KinveyException - if anything goes wrong with the network communication

fetchOne

void fetchOne(T query,
              ScalarCallback<T> callback)
Uses a background thread to retrieve the first entity that matches the properties in the query object. For enhanced query support use EntityCollection.

Parameters:
query - map of key/values to match on the fetch operation
callback - onSuccess will be called with the first entity that matches the query

findBy

void findBy(String property,
            boolean value,
            ScalarCallback<T> callback)
Uses a background thread to find first entity from the cloud service that matches the boolean value.

Parameters:
property - Name of the boolean field to match
value - True or false
callback - onSuccess will be called with the first entity that matches the query

getId

String getId()
The unique identifier for the entity. Returns null if the id property is not there.

Returns:
the unique identifier of the entity, will be null prior to calling persist or fetch.

load

EntityDict load(String id)
                throws KinveyException
Synchronously fetches the given entity by id. Generally the load(String, ScalarCallback) is preferred

All properties currently loaded will be removed and replaced with the object loaded from the cloud service.

Parameters:
id - unique identifier associated with entity for which to fetch
Throws:
KinveyException

load

void load(String id,
          ScalarCallback<T> callback)
Uses a background thread to fetches the given entity by id.

All properties currently loaded will be removed and replaced with the object loaded from the cloud service.

Parameters:
id - unique identifier associated with entity for which to fetch
callback - called with result, callback.onSuccess(null) will be called if entity does not exist

putProperty

void putProperty(String propKey,
                 Object value)
Maps the property key passed in with the value

Parameters:
propKey - Unique key value per instance of this entity
value - Any string
